  <h1>Community Guidelines</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> February 19, 2026</p>
  <p>These guidelines apply to all ratings, comments, and Community posts on Whyyoushould (WYS), operated by <strong>Heisenberg (WYS)</strong>.</p>

  <h2>Age and Safety</h2>
  <p>Accounts are for users 13 and older. Some titles discussed on WYS include mature themes. Keep language and behavior appropriate for a mixed audience.</p>

  <h2>Respect First</h2>
  <p>Debate ideas, not people. Harassment, threats, hate speech, slurs, and personal attacks are not allowed.</p>

  <h2>No Spam or Manipulation</h2>
  <p>Do not post repetitive promotional content, fake engagement, misleading links, or coordinated vote manipulation.</p>

  <h2>Content Quality</h2>
  <p>Community posts should be your own opinion or experience about the specific title. Off-topic dumps, copied reviews, and low-effort abuse may be removed.</p>

  <h2>Privacy and Personal Data</h2>
  <p>Do not post private or identifying information about yourself or others. Do not impersonate another person or brand.</p>

  <h2>User Controls</h2>
  <p>You can edit or delete your own comments and community posts. WYS may remove content or restrict accounts that violate these guidelines or Terms.</p>

  <h2>Moderation</h2>
  <p>Owner moderation can remove harmful or policy-violating content. Repeated or severe violations may lead to account suspension.</p>

  <h2>Reporting</h2>
  <p>If you see abusive or illegal content, contact <strong>Heisenberg (WYS)</strong> with a link and short explanation.</p>
</section>
